WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
FARMERS' MARKET FESTIVITIES 
The Santa Monica Farmers' Market will celebrate its eighth anniversary 
Wednesday from 11 a.m. to 2 p.m. at 2nd Street and Arizona Avenue in downtown 
Santa Monica. 
The market, which operates each Wednesday at that intersection from 10 a.m. to 
3 p.m. during the summer and fall, is one of the largest in the Southland. 
The anniversary celebration will feature music by Freeway Philharmonic, a 
continuous raffle and a cake-cutting ceremony with city officials at noon. 
